citeinfo.title: Gulf of Alaska CTD Data (1978-1979)

abstract.p: CTD data were collected from cruises in the Gulf of Alaska from February 1978 to 1979. These data are high resolution vertical profiles of conductivity, temperature, and pressure. Additional sensors may include dissolved oxygen or other biological/chemical sensors (nephelometers, fluorometers)... The data are stored on 5,592 disk files (34 MB) at the Pacific Marine Environmental Laboratory in Seattle, Washington.
